20. Carding method comprising the following steps: 
feeding a main drum of a carding machine with a first stream of fibre in a thin layer to a first point of interaction with the said main drum; 
feeding the main drum of the carding machine, simultaneously with the said first stream, with a second stream of fibre in a thin layer to a second point of interaction with the said main drum, the said second point of interaction being downstream of the said first point of interaction; 
performing on the fibre carried by the said main drum a first parallelization by means of a first set of moving flats; 
performing on the fibre carried by the said main drum a second parallelization by means of a second set of moving flats situated downstream of the said first set of moving flats; and 
taking the thin layer of parallelized fibre from the main drum by means of a doffer system.

